textAnnotations.description:
NATO Force Intearation Unit Latvia
Providing Security for
Business Growth and Investments
We kindly invite you to our Joint Chamber Luncheon with NATO Force
Integration Unit (NFIU) Latvia. NFIU Commander Colonel Eriks Naglis will
be accompanied by NATO officers from Great Britain, Norway and United
States of America to give an overview of their activities and answer your
questions
Col Eriks Naglis (LAT)
Civilian Jūlija Rumjanceva (LAT)
LtCol Simon Badman (GBR)
Maj Andrew Carrigan (USA)
Maj Bjørn Vikas (NOR)
Maj Beathe-Kristin Andestad (NOR)
NFIU
The presentation will include background for establishment of the
headquarter, the geopolitical situation and an overview of the main tasks
and ongoing activities. It will be followed by Q&A session
September 22, 11:30
Radisson Blu Hotel Daugava, Kuğu Street 24, Room Daugava
Members of the participating chambers EUR 35
Non-members EUR 50
